This paper is about benchmarking graph database systems, which is a topic related to database management (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as graph databases are often used in machine learning applications. The paper also discusses the design and engineering principles of the benchmark, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the generation and manipulation of large graph data sets, which is a topic related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the ability to control the diversity of properties of both the generated graph instances and the generated query workloads, which is a topic related to machine learning and statistics (cs.LG).
